comment: Thompson (CLE) and Valanciunas (TOR) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Carroll (TOR) makes contact with James' (CLE) arm which affects his shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Lowry (TOR) makes contact with Irving's (CLE) arm and affects his SQBR.
Lowry (TOR) is in a legal guarding position when he contests Irving's (CLE) shot attempt.
Smith (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Lowry's (TOR) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Smith (CLE) dislodges Valanciunas (TOR) affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Valanciunas (TOR) sets the screen on Smith (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Patterson (TOR) makes incidental contact with Irving (CLE) that does not affect his FOM.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court was upheld and Cleveland is given possession.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that Toronto signaled for a timeout prior to time expiring in the quarter. The game clock was then reset to 00:00.3.
Patterson (TOR) sets the screen on James (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Valanciunas (TOR) sets the screen on Shumpert (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
